RIGOAL USB4 cables features not only 100W Fast Power Delivery, 5K@60Hz Display, 40Gbps Data Transmission, Compatible Thunderbolt 3, these powerful functions, and the tough design are also fascinating. Metal encased tips and is covered by a thick Aramid-Fiber Braided material, ensuring your cable is long-lasting and tangle-free. No more dreaded splitting or bent ends. Stop wasting your money on cables that don't last.We've heard numerous complaints about charging cables:
    They are cheaply made! 
    They break too easily! 
    They are too short! 
Here are RIGOAL Cables we want to change things with our World’s Strongest & Powerful Aramid-Fiber Braid USB4 Cables.The USB4 specification has four key traits, These include:
Two-lane operation with up to 40Gbps operation (over certified cables), using the USB-C connection;
More efficient sharing between data and display protocols;
Compatibility with USB 3.2, USB 3.1, USB 3.0, USB 2.0, and even Thunderbolt 3;
USB4 offer intelligent Power Delivery at up to 100W. The Power Delivery over USB4 is bi-directional, allowing power to flow to and from a connected device.
Up to 40Gbps Transfers SpeedRIGOAL USB4 cable can transfer data at up to a staggering speed of 40Gbps. You can transfer music, movies, or entire seasons of TV shows in seconds. High volume data capability makes the 40Gbps ideal for high definition video.Single 5K or Dual 4KRIGOAL USB4 cable support crystal clear HD dual monitors at Single 5K (5120 x 2880) @ 60Hz or 4Kx2K(4096x2160) @ 60HZ video resolution. Single cable docking solution to connect a Dock then drive 2 displays.Samsung DeX Desktop ExperiencesTurn your Samsung Galaxy S10/S9/S8/S10+/S9+/S8+ Note 9/8, Huawei Mate 10/10 Pro/20 Connect your smartphones to a monitor, for a desktop experience powered by your phone. So you can turn any place into a workplace. NOTICE: Please update to Andriod 9 System first, then can use the Samsung Dex function (system running configuration).RIGOAL USB4 cable is the perfect travel companion. Allowing you to pack only one cable that fulfills all your needs. Charge you phone, listen to music, play videos from your phone to a TV, transfer photos to your computer at maximum speed. Charge or update your GPS device and many other uses.  Support 5A/100WIt supports power delivery up to 100 Watts, providing fast charging for your MacBook Pro.MacBook Pro (13") is charged to 65% in 30 minutes.One of the few cables on market to support up to 100W Power Delivery & Laptop charging @ 5 Amp 20V = 100W. FAST CHARGE YOUR USB C PHONECHARHE YOUR PADBuilt-in E-Mark ChipWithout E-Mark Chip, USB-C to C cable CANNOT to negotiate up to 100W Power Delivery.NOTE: Some TB3 cables may be rated up to 60W charging only.ULTRA TOUGH ARAMID-FIBER REINFORCEDEach cable is woven with Aramid-Fiber Braid to increase durability and shield from heat. The flexibility of these fibers adds protection and structure without compromising movement to endure years of daily abuse.Crafted With Only Durable MaterialsUSB4 brings data transfers at speeds up to 40Gbps over USB-C, enabling a superset of standard USB-C to truly enable one compact port that does it all  delivering the fastest, most versatile connection to any dock, display, or data device. For the first time, one port can connect numerous Thunderbolt devices, any display, and billions of USB devices (additional adapters may be required).Coaxial cableRigoal USB4 cable used Coaxial cable which allows the cable's copper core to transmit data quickly, without succumbing to interference or damage from environment factors and ensure loading safety.ULTRA TOUGH ARAMID-FIBER REINFORCEDUSB-C to USB-C cable built-in 56 Ω Pull-up Resistor and 22AWG thick copper cores to ensure loading safety. 30,000 times plug test and 30,000 times bending test ensure maximum durability. 5X durable Nylon-Braided cable combined with aluminum alloy shell ensures solid and tangling-free. Excellent choice for a durable and cost-effective USB-C to USB-C cord.Certified  ChipsetRIGOAL USB4 Cable use Convenient Power CPS8821 which is certified by USB-IF (Test ID 4244) PD E maker. It is a high-performance USB-C passive cable electronic label chip (E-marker), which support the latest USB PD3.0 V2.0 version and USB4 features, which is helpful for getting wider-spread support for high capacity USB power delivery. Which is helpful for getting wider-spread support for USB devices.
